type: thesis

title: "Evaluation of the Use of Large Language Models in Information Security Risk Assessment: A Comparative Study with Human Experts"

authors:
  - family-names: "Pinto"
    given-names: "Gustavo Roberto"

year: 2026

institution:
  name: "Federal University of Uberlândia"

department: "School of Computer Science"

thesis-type: "Master's Dissertation"

abstract: >
  This master's dissertation investigates the behavior of Large Language Models
  in information security risk assessment scenarios compared to human experts.
  The study evaluates 18 cybersecurity risk scenarios based on the CIS Critical
  Security Controls and compares assessments produced by five popular LLMs with
  responses provided by 50 cybersecurity and technology professionals. The
  results highlight the importance of human oversight and Human-in-the-Loop
  approaches when applying LLMs to information security risk assessment
  processes.

keywords:
